      "score": 791,
      "comments": 259,
      "author": "maltalex",
      "published": "2026-06-06T04:38:36Z",
      "bullets": [
        "S&P 500's public listing and profitability rules exclude privately held AI giants OpenAI and Anthropic despite their massive market valuations.",
        "OpenAI's capped-profit structure and Anthropic's Public Benefit Corporation status present novel governance hurdles for traditional public market integration.",
        "Exclusion from indices like the S&P 500 limits passive retail and institutional capital inflows for top-tier LLM developers."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
