      "score": 22,
      "comments": 8,
      "author": "weineng",
      "published": "2026-06-06T02:37:28Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Compiling with -nostdlib and replacing main with _start bypasses standard C library overhead, drastically reducing initial ELF binary size.",
        "Using direct assembly system calls (like sys_exit) eliminates runtime dependencies, allowing developers to omit libc linking entirely.",
        "Shrinking binaries to extreme minimums (under 100 bytes) requires manual ELF header manipulation and overlapping header fields using assembly."
      ]
    },
